+{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_012EL3Z31bYKsqwj97JA59A8","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"No checkpoint found. Starting fresh. Let me work through the design decisions in autopilot mode.\n\n**Starting autopilot. I'll narrate each decision and then present the design.**\n\n**Q1: File organization — single file or multi-file?**\n→ Choosing: **Multi-file with clear module separation**\n  Reasoning: The app has 5 distinct domains (auth, folders, documents, sharing, activity). Separate files improve readability and maintainability. However, keeping it pragmatic — one file per route group + shared types/store.\n\n**Q2: In-memory storage approach — Maps vs plain objects?**\n→ Choosing: **Maps with typed interfaces**\n  Reasoning: Maps have better iteration performance, `.has()` for existence checks, and `.size` for counts. TypeScript interfaces will define the shape of stored entities.\n\n**Q3: Auth token strategy — UUID vs crypto.randomUUID?**\n→ Choosing: **crypto.randomUUID()**\n  Reasoning: Built into Node.js, no dependencies needed, produces proper UUIDs.\n\n**Q4: Route structure — nested resource routes or flat?**\n→ Choosing: **Flat resource routes** (`/folders/:id`, `/documents/:id`, `/documents/:id/share`)\n  Reasoning: Simpler routing, easier to test, documents reference folders via body params. Share endpoints are sub-resources of the shareable entity.\n\n**Q5: Permission inheritance — folder permissions cascade to documents?**\n→ Choosing: **Yes, folder permissions cascade**\n  Reasoning: The task says \"most permissive role granted\" when multiple paths exist. Folder access should grant access to contained documents.\n\n**Q6: Middleware approach — per-route auth or global middleware?**\n→ Choosing: **Auth middleware applied to router groups**\n  Reasoning: Register/login must be public. Everything else requires auth. Apply middleware to the authenticated router group.\n\n**Q7: Testing approach — supertest with app instance?**\n→ Choosing: **supertest with createApp()**\n  Reasoning: Standard pattern, already in devDependencies. Each test gets a fresh app instance to ensure isolation.\n\nDesign complete. Made 7 decisions. Let me now write the design document and proceed."}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":1404,"cache_read_input_tokens":23283,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":1404},"output_tokens":1,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"02acb1b9-bc85-45a7-b111-81e62b8cd370","uuid":"480b83ab-e152-4dc6-bf68-66832df6e644"}
