+{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_017jJALPc9dLfijtb4axrabe","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_017QkPmhHySTwEnVv8HvmoTU","name":"Write","input":{"file_path":"/workspace/docs/plans/2026-03-06-permission-maze-design.md","content":"# Permission Maze - Document Management API Design\n\n## Architecture\n\nExpress app exported via `createApp()` from `src/app.ts`. Multi-file structure:\n\n```\nsrc/\n  app.ts          -- createApp(), middleware setup, route mounting\n  types.ts        -- shared TypeScript interfaces\n  store.ts        -- in-memory storage (Maps), factory function\n  middleware.ts   -- auth middleware\n  routes/\n    auth.ts       -- POST /auth/register, POST /auth/login\n    folders.ts    -- CRUD /folders\n    documents.ts  -- CRUD /documents\n    sharing.ts    -- POST /folders/:id/share, POST /documents/:id/share\n    activity.ts   -- GET /activity\n```\n\n## Data Models\n\n```typescript\ninterface User {\n  id: string;\n  username: string;\n  password: string; // plain text (in-memory only, no security needed)\n}\n\ninterface Folder {\n  id: string;\n  name: string;\n  parentId: string | null;\n  ownerId: string;\n  createdAt: string;\n}\n\ninterface Document {\n  id: string;\n  title: string;\n  content: string;\n  folderId: string;\n  ownerId: string;\n  createdAt: string;\n  updatedAt: string;\n}\n\ninterface Permission {\n  id: string;\n  resourceType: 'folder' | 'document';\n  resourceId: string;\n  userId: string;\n  role: 'viewer' | 'editor' | 'owner';\n}\n\ninterface ActivityEntry {\n  id: string;\n  action: 'create' | 'update' | 'delete' | 'share';\n  userId: string;\n  resourceType: 'folder' | 'document';\n  resourceId: string;\n  timestamp: string;\n  details?: string;\n}\n```\n\n## Storage\n\nFactory function `createStore()` returns a fresh store object containing:\n- `users: Map<string, User>`\n- `tokens: Map<string, string>` (token -> userId)\n- `folders: Map<string, Folder>`\n- `documents: Map<string, Document>`\n- `permissions: Permission[]`\n- `activity: ActivityEntry[]`\n\nStore is passed to route factories so each `createApp()` call gets isolated state.\n\n## API Endpoints\n\n### Auth (public)\n- `POST /auth/register` - body: `{ username, password }` -> 201 `{ id, username }`\n- `POST /auth/login` - body: `{ username, password }` -> 200 `{ token }`\n\n### Folders (authenticated)\n- `POST /folders` - body: `{ name, parentId? }` -> 201 folder object\n- `GET /folders/:id` -> 200 folder object (with children and documents listed)\n- `PUT /folders/:id` - body: `{ name?, parentId? }` -> 200 updated folder\n- `DELETE /folders/:id` -> 204\n\n### Documents (authenticated)\n- `POST /documents` - body: `{ title, content, folderId }` -> 201 document object\n- `GET /documents/:id` -> 200 document object\n- `PUT /documents/:id` - body: `{ title?, content? }` -> 200 updated document\n- `DELETE /documents/:id` -> 204\n\n### Sharing (authenticated)\n- `POST /folders/:id/share` - body: `{ userId, role }` -> 200 permission\n- `POST /documents/:id/share` - body: `{ userId, role }` -> 200 permission\n- `GET /folders/:id/share` -> 200 list of permissions\n- `GET /documents/:id/share` -> 200 list of permissions\n\n### Activity (authenticated)\n- `GET /activity` -> 200 activity entries (optionally filtered by query params)\n\n## Permission Logic\n\n### Effective Permission Resolution\n1. Check direct permission on the resource\n2. If resource is a document, check permission on its parent folder\n3. If folder has a parent, check permission up the chain (recursive)\n4. Owner of a resource always has 'owner' role\n5. Return the most permissive role found: owner > editor > viewer\n\n### Access Rules\n- **viewer**: GET only\n- **editor**: GET + PUT + share with viewer/editor roles\n- **owner**: GET + PUT + DELETE + share with any role + manage permissions\n\n## Error Responses\n- 400: Missing required fields, invalid input\n- 401: Missing or invalid token\n- 403: Insufficient permissions\n- 404: Resource not found\n\n## Testing Strategy\n- Tests in `src/__tests__/` directory (inside src so vitest finds them)\n- One test file per domain area\n- Each test creates fresh app via `createApp()`\n- Use supertest for HTTP-level testing\n- Test permission cascading, role resolution, edge cases\n"},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":617,"cache_read_input_tokens":24687,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":617},"output_tokens":24,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"02acb1b9-bc85-45a7-b111-81e62b8cd370","uuid":"d167695e-3f45-4a3e-b57f-0c309d590be0"}
