+{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_012NtzsYkESAiatgSCS9tAvV","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_01StskXtz7uw7QN6FMKDCPLU","name":"Write","input":{"file_path":"/workspace/docs/plans/2026-03-06-permission-maze-plan.md","content":"# Permission Maze Implementation Plan\n\n> **For Claude:** REQUIRED SUB-SKILL: Use conclave:executing-plans to implement this plan task-by-task.\n\n**Goal:** Build a document management API with user auth, hierarchical folders, documents, granular sharing permissions, and activity logging.\n\n**Architecture:** Express app with `createApp()` factory pattern. Multi-file structure: types, store, middleware, and route modules. In-memory Maps for storage, passed via store object to route factories for test isolation.\n\n**Tech Stack:** Express 4, TypeScript (ES2022, Node16 modules), Vitest + Supertest for testing.\n\n---\n\n### Task 1: Types and Store\n\n**Files:**\n- Create: `src/types.ts`\n- Create: `src/store.ts`\n\n**Dependencies:** none\n\n**Step 1: Create type definitions**\n\nCreate `src/types.ts`:\n\n```typescript\nexport interface User {\n  id: string;\n  username: string;\n  password: string;\n}\n\nexport interface Folder {\n  id: string;\n  name: string;\n  parentId: string | null;\n  ownerId: string;\n  createdAt: string;\n}\n\nexport interface Doc {\n  id: string;\n  title: string;\n  content: string;\n  folderId: string;\n  ownerId: string;\n  createdAt: string;\n  updatedAt: string;\n}\n\nexport type Role = 'viewer' | 'editor' | 'owner';\nexport type ResourceType = 'folder' | 'document';\n\nexport interface Permission {\n  id: string;\n  resourceType: ResourceType;\n  resourceId: string;\n  userId: string;\n  role: Role;\n}\n\nexport interface ActivityEntry {\n  id: string;\n  action: 'create' | 'update' | 'delete' | 'share';\n  userId: string;\n  resourceType: ResourceType;\n  resourceId: string;\n  timestamp: string;\n  details?: string;\n}\n\nexport interface Store {\n  users: Map<string, User>;\n  usersByUsername: Map<string, User>;\n  tokens: Map<string, string>;\n  folders: Map<string, Folder>;\n  documents: Map<string, Doc>;\n  permissions: Permission[];\n  activity: ActivityEntry[];\n}\n```\n\n**Step 2: Create store factory**\n\nCreate `src/store.ts`:\n\n```typescript\nimport { Store } from './types.js';\n\nexport function createStore(): Store {\n  return {\n    users: new Map(),\n    usersByUsername: new Map(),\n    tokens: new Map(),\n    folders: new Map(),\n    documents: new Map(),\n    permissions: [],\n    activity: [],\n  };\n}\n```\n\n**Step 3: Verify build**\n\nRun: `npx tsc --noEmit`\nExpected: No errors.\n\n**Step 4: Commit**\n\n```bash\ngit add src/types.ts src/store.ts\ngit commit -m \"feat: add type definitions and store factory\"\n```\n\n---\n\n### Task 2: Auth Middleware and Auth Routes\n\n**Files:**\n- Create: `src/middleware.ts`\n- Create: `src/routes/auth.ts`\n- Create: `src/app.ts`\n- Create: `src/__tests__/auth.test.ts`\n\n**Dependencies:** Task 1\n\n**Step 1: Write auth tests**\n\nCreate `src/__tests__/auth.test.ts`:\n\n```typescript\nimport { describe, it, expect, beforeEach } from 'vitest';\nimport request from 'supertest';\nimport type { Express } from 'express';\nimport { createApp } from '../app.js';\n\ndescribe('Auth', () => {\n  let app: Express;\n\n  beforeEach(() => {\n    app = createApp();\n  });\n\n  describe('POST /auth/register', () => {\n    it('should register a new user', async () => {\n      const res = await request(app)\n        .post('/auth/register')\n        .send({ username: 'alice', password: 'pass123' });\n      expect(res.status).toBe(201);\n      expect(res.body).toHaveProperty('id');\n      expect(res.body.username).toBe('alice');\n      expect(res.body).not.toHaveProperty('password');\n    });\n\n    it('should reject duplicate username', async () => {\n      await request(app).post('/auth/register').send({ username: 'alice', password: 'pass123' });\n      const res = await request(app).post('/auth/register').send({ username: 'alice', password: 'pass456' });\n      expect(res.status).toBe(409);\n    });\n\n    it('should reject missing fields', async () => {\n      const res = await request(app).post('/auth/register').send({ username: 'alice' });\n      expect(res.status).toBe(400);\n    });\n  });\n\n  describe('POST /auth/login', () => {\n    it('should login and return token', async () => {\n      await request(app).post('/auth/register').send({ username: 'alice', password: 'pass123' });\n      const res = await request(app).post('/auth/login').send({ username: 'alice', password: 'pass123' });\n      expect(res.status).toBe(200);\n      expect(res.body).toHaveProperty('token');\n    });\n\n    it('should reject wrong password', async () => {\n      await request(app).post('/auth/register').send({ username: 'alice', password: 'pass123' });\n      const res = await request(app).post('/auth/login').send({ username: 'alice', password: 'wrong' });\n      expect(res.status).toBe(401);\n    });\n\n    it('should reject non-existent user', async () => {\n      const res = await request(app).post('/auth/login').send({ username: 'nobody', password: 'pass' });\n      expect(res.status).toBe(401);\n    });\n  });\n\n  describe('Auth middleware', () => {\n    it('should reject requests without token', async () => {\n      const res = await request(app).get('/folders/some-id');\n      expect(res.status).toBe(401);\n    });\n\n    it('should reject invalid token', async () => {\n      const res = await request(app).get('/folders/some-id').set('Authorization', 'Bearer invalid');\n      expect(res.status).toBe(401);\n    });\n  });\n});\n```\n\n**Step 2: Run tests to verify they fail**\n\nRun: `npx vitest run src/__tests__/auth.test.ts`\nExpected: FAIL (createApp doesn't exist yet)\n\n**Step 3: Implement auth middleware**\n\nCreate `src/middleware.ts`:\n\n```typescript\nimport { Request, Response, NextFunction } from 'express';\nimport { Store } from './types.js';\n\nexport interface AuthRequest extends Request {\n  userId?: string;\n}\n\nexport function authMiddleware(store: Store) {\n  return (req: AuthRequest, res: Response, next: NextFunction): void => {\n    const header = req.headers.authorization;\n    if (!header || !header.startsWith('Bearer ')) {\n      res.status(401).json({ error: 'Authentication required' });\n      return;\n    }\n    const token = header.slice(7);\n    const userId = store.tokens.get(token);\n    if (!userId) {\n      res.status(401).json({ error: 'Invalid token' });\n      return;\n    }\n    req.userId = userId;\n    next();\n  };\n}\n```\n\n**Step 4: Implement auth routes**\n\nCreate `src/routes/auth.ts`:\n\n```typescript\nimport { Router } from 'express';\nimport crypto from 'node:crypto';\nimport { Store } from '../types.js';\n\nexport function authRoutes(store: Store): Router {\n  const router = Router();\n\n  router.post('/register', (req, res) => {\n    const { username, password } = req.body;\n    if (!username || !password) {\n      res.status(400).json({ error: 'Username and password required' });\n      return;\n    }\n    if (store.usersByUsername.has(username)) {\n      res.status(409).json({ error: 'Username already exists' });\n      return;\n    }\n    const id = crypto.randomUUID();\n    const user = { id, username, password };\n    store.users.set(id, user);\n    store.usersByUsername.set(username, user);\n    res.status(201).json({ id, username });\n  });\n\n  router.post('/login', (req, res) => {\n    const { username, password } = req.body;\n    if (!username || !password) {\n      res.status(400).json({ error: 'Username and password required' });\n      return;\n    }\n    const user = store.usersByUsername.get(username);\n    if (!user || user.password !== password) {\n      res.status(401).json({ error: 'Invalid credentials' });\n      return;\n    }\n    const token = crypto.randomUUID();\n    store.tokens.set(token, user.id);\n    res.status(200).json({ token });\n  });\n\n  return router;\n}\n```\n\n**Step 5: Create app.ts**\n\nCreate `src/app.ts`:\n\n```typescript\nimport express from 'express';\nimport { createStore } from './store.js';\nimport { authMiddleware } from './middleware.js';\nimport { authRoutes } from './routes/auth.js';\n\nexport function createApp() {\n  const app = express();\n  const store = createStore();\n\n  app.use(express.json());\n\n  // Public routes\n  app.use('/auth', authRoutes(store));\n\n  // Protected routes - add auth middleware\n  app.use(authMiddleware(store));\n\n  return app;\n}\n```\n\n**Step 6: Run tests**\n\nRun: `npx vitest run src/__tests__/auth.test.ts`\nExpected: All PASS\n\n**Step 7: Commit**\n\n```bash\ngit add src/middleware.ts src/routes/auth.ts src/app.ts src/__tests__/auth.test.ts\ngit commit -m \"feat: add auth registration, login, and middleware\"\n```\n\n---\n\n### Task 3: Permission Helper\n\n**Files:**\n- Create: `src/permissions.ts`\n- Create: `src/__tests__/permissions.test.ts`\n\n**Dependencies:** Task 1\n\n**Step 1: Write permission helper tests**\n\nCreate `src/__tests__/permissions.test.ts` testing:\n- Owner of resource gets 'owner' role\n- Direct permission on resource\n- Document inherits folder permission\n- Folder inherits parent folder permission (recursive)\n- Most permissive role wins when multiple paths\n- No access returns null\n\nUse `createStore()` directly, populate with test data, and call `getEffectiveRole()`.\n\n**Step 2: Run tests to verify they fail**\n\n**Step 3: Implement permission helpers**\n\nCreate `src/permissions.ts`:\n\n```typescript\nimport { Store, Role } from './types.js';\n\nconst ROLE_PRIORITY: Record<Role, number> = { viewer: 1, editor: 2, owner: 3 };\n\nfunction higherRole(a: Role | null, b: Role | null): Role | null {\n  if (!a) return b;\n  if (!b) return a;\n  return ROLE_PRIORITY[a] >= ROLE_PRIORITY[b] ? a : b;\n}\n\nexport function getEffectiveRole(\n  store: Store,\n  userId: string,\n  resourceType: 'folder' | 'document',\n  resourceId: string\n): Role | null {\n  let role: Role | null = null;\n\n  // Check ownership\n  if (resourceType === 'document') {\n    const doc = store.documents.get(resourceId);\n    if (doc && doc.ownerId === userId) role = 'owner';\n  } else {\n    const folder = store.folders.get(resourceId);\n    if (folder && folder.ownerId === userId) role = 'owner';\n  }\n\n  // Check direct permissions\n  for (const p of store.permissions) {\n    if (p.resourceType === resourceType && p.resourceId === resourceId && p.userId === userId) {\n      role = higherRole(role, p.role);\n    }\n  }\n\n  // If document, check parent folder chain\n  if (resourceType === 'document') {\n    const doc = store.documents.get(resourceId);\n    if (doc) {\n      const folderRole = getEffectiveRole(store, userId, 'folder', doc.folderId);\n      role = higherRole(role, folderRole);\n    }\n  }\n\n  // If folder, check parent folder chain\n  if (resourceType === 'folder') {\n    const folder = store.folders.get(resourceId);\n    if (folder && folder.parentId) {\n      const parentRole = getEffectiveRole(store, userId, 'folder', folder.parentId);\n      role = higherRole(role, parentRole);\n    }\n  }\n\n  return role;\n}\n\nexport function canRead(role: Role | null): boolean {\n  return role !== null;\n}\n\nexport function canEdit(role: Role | null): boolean {\n  return role === 'editor' || role === 'owner';\n}\n\nexport function canDelete(role: Role | null): boolean {\n  return role === 'owner';\n}\n\nexport function canShare(role: Role | null): boolean {\n  return role === 'editor' || role === 'owner';\n}\n\nexport function canShareRole(userRole: Role | null, targetRole: Role): boolean {\n  if (userRole === 'owner') return true;\n  if (userRole === 'editor') return targetRole === 'viewer' || targetRole === 'editor';\n  return false;\n}\n```\n\n**Step 4: Run tests**\n\n**Step 5: Commit**\n\n```bash\ngit add src/permissions.ts src/__tests__/permissions.test.ts\ngit commit -m \"feat: add permission resolution with folder inheritance\"\n```\n\n---\n\n### Task 4: Folder Routes\n\n**Files:**\n- Create: `src/routes/folders.ts`\n- Create: `src/__tests__/folders.test.ts`\n- Modify: `src/app.ts` (mount folder routes)\n\n**Dependencies:** Task 2, Task 3\n\n**Step 1: Write folder tests**\n\nTest cases:\n- Create a folder (returns 201, folder object)\n- Create nested folder with parentId\n- Get folder by id (returns folder + children + documents)\n- Get folder - 404 for non-existent\n- Update folder name\n- Delete folder (owner only)\n- Reject creation with missing name\n- Reject access for user without permission\n- Parent folder permission cascades to child\n\n**Step 2: Run tests to verify they fail**\n\n**Step 3: Implement folder routes**\n\nCreate `src/routes/folders.ts` with Router factory accepting store. Implement:\n- `POST /` - create folder, add owner permission, log activity\n- `GET /:id` - get folder with children/docs (check read permission)\n- `PUT /:id` - update folder (check edit permission)\n- `DELETE /:id` - delete folder (check owner permission), also delete child resources\n\n**Step 4: Mount in app.ts**\n\nAdd to `src/app.ts` after auth middleware:\n```typescript\nimport { folderRoutes } from './routes/folders.js';\napp.use('/folders', folderRoutes(store));\n```\n\n**Step 5: Run tests**\n\n**Step 6: Commit**\n\n```bash\ngit add src/routes/folders.ts src/__tests__/folders.test.ts src/app.ts\ngit commit -m \"feat: add folder CRUD with permission checks\"\n```\n\n---\n\n### Task 5: Document Routes\n\n**Files:**\n- Create: `src/routes/documents.ts`\n- Create: `src/__tests__/documents.test.ts`\n- Modify: `src/app.ts` (mount document routes)\n\n**Dependencies:** Task 4\n\n**Step 1: Write document tests**\n\nTest cases:\n- Create document in folder (201, doc object with timestamps)\n- Get document by id\n- Update document title/content (updatedAt changes)\n- Delete document (owner only)\n- Reject creation without folderId\n