target user exists, validate role, add permission, log activity\n- `POST /documents/:id/share` - same pattern\n- `GET /folders/:id/share` - list permissions for folder (requires read access)\n- `GET /documents/:id/share` - list permissions for doc (requires read access)\n\n**Step 4: Mount in app.ts**\n\n```typescript\nimport { sharingRoutes } from './routes/sharing.js';\napp.use('/', sharingRoutes(store));\n```\n\n**Step 5: Run tests**\n\n**Step 6: Commit**\n\n```bash\ngit add src/routes/sharing.ts src/__tests__/sharing.test.ts src/app.ts\ngit commit -m \"feat: add sharing endpoints with role-based access control\"\n```\n\n---\n\n### Task 7: Activity Log Route\n\n**Files:**\n- Create: `src/routes/activity.ts`\n- Create: `src/__tests__/activity.test.ts`\n- Modify: `src/app.ts` (mount activity routes)\n\n**Dependencies:** Task 6\n\n**Step 1: Write activity tests**\n\nTest cases:\n- Activity log records document creation\n- Activity log records document update\n- Activity log records document deletion\n- Activity log records share events\n- GET /activity returns all activity for the authenticated user\n- Activity entries have correct structure (action, userId, resourceType, resourceId, timestamp)\n\n**Step 2: Run tests to verify they fail**\n\n**Step 3: Implement activity route**\n\nCreate `src/routes/activity.ts`:\n- `GET /` - return activity entries, optionally filtered by query params (resourceType, action)\n\n**Step 4: Mount in app.ts**\n\n```typescript\nimport { activityRoutes } from './routes/activity.js';\napp.use('/activity', activityRoutes(store));\n```\n\n**Step 5: Run tests**\n\n**Step 6: Commit**\n\n```bash\ngit add src/routes/activity.ts src/__tests__/activity.test.ts src/app.ts\ngit commit -m \"feat: add activity log endpoint\"\n```\n\n---\n\n### Task 8: Integration Tests and Final Verification\n\n**Files:**\n- Create: `src/__tests__/integration.test.ts`\n\n**Dependencies:** Task 7\n\n**Step 1: Write integration tests**\n\nTest end-to-end flows:\n- Full flow: register two users, create folder, create document, share with second user, second user reads document\n- Permission cascade: share folder, verify user can read all documents in it\n- Nested folders: create parent > child > document, share parent, verify access to nested document\n- Most permissive role: give user viewer on folder + editor on document, verify editor wins\n- Owner always has full access even without explicit permission entry\n- Activity log captures all actions in correct order\n\n**Step 2: Run all tests**\n\nRun: `npx vitest run`\nExpected: All PASS\n\n**Step 3: Run build**\n\nRun: `npx tsc --noEmit`\nExpected: No errors\n\n**Step 4: Run lint**\n\nRun: `npx eslint src/`\nExpected: No errors\n\n**Step 5: Commit**\n\n```bash\ngit add src/__tests__/integration.test.ts\ngit commit -m \"feat: add integration tests for end-to-end flows\"\n```\n\n---\n\n## Execution Order\n\nTasks 1 → 2 + 3 (parallel) → 4 → 5 → 6 → 7 → 8\n\nWave 1: Task 1 (types + store)\nWave 2: Task 2 (auth) + Task 3 (permissions) — independent, can run in parallel\nWave 3: Task 4 (folders) — depends on auth + permissions\nWave 4: Task 5 (documents) — depends on folders\nWave 5: Task 6 (sharing) — depends on folders + documents\nWave 6: Task 7 (activity) — depends on sharing\nWave 7: Task 8 (integration) — depends on everything\n","structuredPatch":[],"originalFile":null}}
